{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, there are ongoing debates in research on generative AI about how we evaluate the accuracy of such systems.",
    "They may be incorrect when identifying concepts, as hallucination can cause the answer to be a reflection of the knowledge model derived from training data rather than the text input.",
    "They could also report relations that do not exist, or with the wrong type of causation.",
    "Automatic (often based on string-matching) and human evaluations (e.g.",
    "via crowdworkers) have shortcomings (Xu et al., 2023) to assess factuality."
  ]
}